      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "@Green Ash The length of the byte array -- getBytes() -- and x.length MAY be equal but is not guaranteed to be so. It will be equal if all the characters are represented by a single byte each. This will always hold true for character encodings that use a single byte per character (or less), such as ISO-8859-1. UTF-8 uses either 1 or 2 bytes, so it depends on the exact characters in the string. Then there are character encodings that always use two bytes per character."
