      "body" : "I&#39;ve updated this answer to show some specific encoded sizes of both &quot;ASCII&quot; characters, and higher-plane characters.  And note that in the latter example, UTF-8 does indeed use 3 bytes per character.  @Green, as I noted at the end you should rarely (if ever) omit the character set, because then your answer isn&#39;t that useful - you don&#39;t know which character set you have the size in."
